      • apptOverlapsForCustomer

        public static boolean apptOverlapsForCustomer​(Customer apptCustomer,
                                              java.time.LocalDateTime apptStart,
                                              java.time.LocalDateTime apptEnd,
                                              int newApptID)
        checks for any appointment overlaps for a customer against a proposed new appointment inspiration for condition from: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/56732882/how-to-check-if-one-date-period-overlapping-another-date-period
        Parameters:
        apptCustomer - is the customer to look for any existing appointments against
        apptStart - is the proposed new appointment start datetime
        apptEnd - is the proposed new appointment end datetime
        Returns:
        true if the appointment overlaps with an existing one and false if no overlap

      • checkForUpcomingAppts

        public static void checkForUpcomingAppts()
        displays an alert for any upcoming appointments in 15 minutes or any appointments that are currently in progress. also lets the user know there are not any in next 15 minutes or in progress if there are not any.
